HEADWORD: Heterocercy
<hw>Het"er*o*cer`cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hetero-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a tail.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Unequal development of the tail lobes of fishes; the possession of
a heterocercal tail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

